Nuages is a package for 3D reconstruction from parallel
cross-sectional data. It uses the Delaunay triangulation.

Input : a set of simple closed polygons on parallel planes.
-----   There may be several (nested) polygons per plane.

Output: A set of triangles representing the surface of a 3D poly-
------  hedra, and/or a set of tetrahedra filling the 3D polyhedra.
        The program adds vertices onto and inside the contours.


This directory contains the executable files:

NUAGES_SunOS_4.1.3_U1.tar.Z    SunOS_4
NUAGES_SunOS_5.5.tar.Z         Solaris
NUAGES_IRIX_5.3.tar.Z          SGI  IRIX 5.3
NUAGES_IRIX_6.2.tar.Z          SGI  IRIX 6.2
NUAGES_HP-UX_10.20.tar.Z       HP UX 10.20
NUAGES_SGI.tar.Z               SGI  IRIX 4.0.5           (*)
NUAGES_DEC.tar.Z               Decstation  (ultrix)      (*)
NUAGES_LINUX.tar.Z                                       (*)
NUAGES_RS6000.tar.Z            IBM RS6000 Aix            (*)

(*) May not be the most recent version. See the included CHANGES file.

